definitions.text:
ABIHA'IL (father of strength, i. e. the strong one). 
(1). The father of Zuriel, " chief of the . . . house of the families of Marari." Num 3:35. (2). The wife of Abishur. 1 Chr 2:29. (3). The son of Huri, of the tribe of Gad. 1 Chr 5:14. (4). The wife of Rehoboam. 2 Chr 11:18. (5). The father of Esther. Esth 2:15; 
Esth  9:29.
